  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The proposed works, by reason of their detrimental impact on historic fabric, dominant size of extension, unsympathetic design, siting and form and lack of information as to impact on heritage assets, would from a dominant and discordant addition to the host building and wider listed terrace  be readily visible from the private realm whilst adversely affect the character and special architectural and historic interest of the listed building whilst failing preserve the character and appearance of Duncan Terrace / Colebrook Row Conservation Area. The works would, therefore cause harm to the significance of the heritage assets, with no public benefit which outweighs this harm, contrary to Chapter 16 (conserving and enhancing the historic environment) of the National Planning Policy Framework 2019, policies D4 and HC1 (Heritage Conservation and Growth) of the London Plan 2021, policies CS8 and CS9 of Islington's Core Strategy 2011, policies DM2.1 and DM2.3 of Islington's Development Management Policies 2013 guidance contained within Islington's Conservation Area Design Guidelines 2002 and Islington's Urban Design Guide 2017."
